<p>A selection of school science videos.&nbsp;&nbsp; These helpful resources can be used in schools or in addition to school and homestudy.&nbsp; They include short video instructional films on wind power, electricity, C60, transistors, nanotubes, bucky ball workshops (C60), states of matter workshops (solids, liquids and gases), short science video career profiles showing the day in the life of a group of young scientists and down-loadable work sheets.</p><table width="100%"><tr><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>A set of short instructional science and engineering&nbsp; videos by BBC Rough Scientist Jonathan Hare to be used for viewing in schools, workshops and in home-study&nbsp; with accompanying information.&nbsp; This project was supported by the <a href=`http://www.leverhulme.ac.uk/`>Leverhulme Trust.</a>&nbsp; Jonathan is available to help with any questions, go on-line to participate in workshops or to give school or college talks.&nbsp; Please email J.P.Hare `at` Sussex.ac.uk (replacing `at` with `@`) for further information.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>A set of short instructional science and engineering&nbsp; videos by BBC Rough Scientist Jonathan Hare to be used for viewing in schools, workshops and in home-study&nbsp; with accompanying information.&nbsp; This project was supported by the <a href=`http://www.leverhulme.ac.uk/`>Leverhulme Trust.</a>&nbsp; Jonathan is available to help with any questions, go on-line to participate in workshops or to give school or college talks.&nbsp; Please email J.P.Hare `at` Sussex.ac.uk (replacing `at` with `@`) for further information.</p>')" href="../subseries/27"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/windmill150.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Scientist Sir Harry Kroto has given workshops around the world in his quest to engage a range of age groups in learning about science.&nbsp; In these video recordings you can hear about everything from galaxy formation and fullerenes, to juggling, politics and tortoises.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Scientist Sir Harry Kroto has given workshops around the world in his quest to engage a range of age groups in learning about science.&nbsp; In these video recordings you can hear about everything from galaxy formation and fullerenes, to juggling, politics and tortoises.</p>')" href="../subseries/29"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/buckyballworkshop3.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Short science videos on solids, liquids and and gases by scientist John Murrell.&nbsp; Originally designed as an experimental video for primary school teachers to show in the classroom, this video may also be of benefit to primary school teachers in terms of thinking about new ways to teach states of matter topics in an interactive manner.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Short science videos on solids, liquids and and gases by scientist John Murrell.&nbsp; Originally designed as an experimental video for primary school teachers to show in the classroom, this video may also be of benefit to primary school teachers in terms of thinking about new ways to teach states of matter topics in an interactive manner.</p>')" href="../subseries/30"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/statesofmatter1.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Have you ever wondered what it is like to work in science?&nbsp; This series of videos gives us a idea.&nbsp; Here fourteen young scientists show us their different careers in science from engineer to physicist to mathematician to surgeon.&nbsp; As you will see entry into a science career can involve a varied route and some unexpected but pleasant results!</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Have you ever wondered what it is like to work in science?&nbsp; This series of videos gives us a idea.&nbsp; Here fourteen young scientists show us their different careers in science from engineer to physicist to mathematician to surgeon.&nbsp; As you will see entry into a science career can involve a varied route and some unexpected but pleasant results!</p>')" href="../subseries/37"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/Snapshotengxlarge.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td></tr><tr><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>A set of short instructional science and engineering&nbsp; videos by BBC Rough Scientist Jonathan Hare to be used for viewing in schools, workshops and in home-study&nbsp; with accompanying information.&nbsp; This project was supported by the <a href=`http://www.leverhulme.ac.uk/`>Leverhulme Trust.</a>&nbsp; Jonathan is available to help with any questions, go on-line to participate in workshops or to give school or college talks.&nbsp; Please email J.P.Hare `at` Sussex.ac.uk (replacing `at` with `@`) for further information.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>A set of short instructional science and engineering&nbsp; videos by BBC Rough Scientist Jonathan Hare to be used for viewing in schools, workshops and in home-study&nbsp; with accompanying information.&nbsp; This project was supported by the <a href=`http://www.leverhulme.ac.uk/`>Leverhulme Trust.</a>&nbsp; Jonathan is available to help with any questions, go on-line to participate in workshops or to give school or college talks.&nbsp; Please email J.P.Hare `at` Sussex.ac.uk (replacing `at` with `@`) for further information.</p>')" href="../subseries/27">Instructional Science and Engineering Videos by Jonathan Hare</a></td><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Scientist Sir Harry Kroto has given workshops around the world in his quest to engage a range of age groups in learning about science.&nbsp; In these video recordings you can hear about everything from galaxy formation and fullerenes, to juggling, politics and tortoises.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Scientist Sir Harry Kroto has given workshops around the world in his quest to engage a range of age groups in learning about science.&nbsp; In these video recordings you can hear about everything from galaxy formation and fullerenes, to juggling, politics and tortoises.</p>')" href="../subseries/29">Buckyball Workshops</a></td><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Short science videos on solids, liquids and and gases by scientist John Murrell.&nbsp; Originally designed as an experimental video for primary school teachers to show in the classroom, this video may also be of benefit to primary school teachers in terms of thinking about new ways to teach states of matter topics in an interactive manner.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Short science videos on solids, liquids and and gases by scientist John Murrell.&nbsp; Originally designed as an experimental video for primary school teachers to show in the classroom, this video may also be of benefit to primary school teachers in terms of thinking about new ways to teach states of matter topics in an interactive manner.</p>')" href="../subseries/30">States of Matter Videos</a></td><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>Have you ever wondered what it is like to work in science?&nbsp; This series of videos gives us a idea.&nbsp; Here fourteen young scientists show us their different careers in science from engineer to physicist to mathematician to surgeon.&nbsp; As you will see entry into a science career can involve a varied route and some unexpected but pleasant results!</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>Have you ever wondered what it is like to work in science?&nbsp; This series of videos gives us a idea.&nbsp; Here fourteen young scientists show us their different careers in science from engineer to physicist to mathematician to surgeon.&nbsp; As you will see entry into a science career can involve a varied route and some unexpected but pleasant results!</p>')" href="../subseries/37">Snapshots - Science Career Videos</a></td></tr><tr><td class="table_top_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>During a three year research project looking at how to make a tiny gas sensor from carbon nanotubes two of the young research scientists decided to try and explain to us what carbon nanotubes are.&nbsp; Here are 5 short science video programmes in Spanish and English doing just that.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>During a three year research project looking at how to make a tiny gas sensor from carbon nanotubes two of the young research scientists decided to try and explain to us what carbon nanotubes are.&nbsp; Here are 5 short science video programmes in Spanish and English doing just that.</p>')" href="../subseries/52"><img height="100"  src="../../images/series_system/nanoseries4.jpg_100x100.jpeg" width="100" border="0" /></a></td></tr><tr><td class="table_bottom_spacer" valign="top" align="center" width="25%"><a title='<p>During a three year research project looking at how to make a tiny gas sensor from carbon nanotubes two of the young research scientists decided to try and explain to us what carbon nanotubes are.&nbsp; Here are 5 short science video programmes in Spanish and English doing just that.</p>' onmouseover="return escape('<p>During a three year research project looking at how to make a tiny gas sensor from carbon nanotubes two of the young research scientists decided to try and explain to us what carbon nanotubes are.&nbsp; Here are 5 short science video programmes in Spanish and English doing just that.</p>')" href="../subseries/52">Carbon Nanotubes</a></td></tr></table><br />&nbsp;<br /><br /><span c